OL,6,F"His family have lost a loving and
OL,7,Fdoting father, husband and son. His
OL,8,Ffriends and fellow Rangers will miss a
OL,9,Fmuch-loved and respected leader.
OL,11,F"The Army has lost a professional,
OL,12,Fcapable, and loyal Special Operations
OL,13,Fsoldier, whose contribution to the
OL,14,Fteam made it much stronger than the
OL,15,Fsum of its parts; he made a real
OL,16,Fimpact throughout his distinguished
OL,17,Fcareer.
OL,19,F"Our thoughts are with his family at
OL,20,Fthis incredibly difficult time. A
OL,21,Fchosen man never forgotten."
